<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="394" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8202a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Officers in All Countries
                                        except Spain</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-15">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>In pursuance of resolution mentioned in Department’s circular
                                telegrams December 7 and 11, President proclaimed on December 11
                                that a state of war exists between United States and the Imperial
                                and Royal Austro-Hungarian Government.<note n="1" xml:id="d394fn1">The proclamation, dealing almost entirely with the treatment of
                                    enemy aliens, is printed in the section relating to that subject
                                    in <ref target="frus1918Supp02">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1918, Supplement
                                        2</ref>.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>